# Pre-push gate — typecheck + the full lint chain + tests must pass
# before push. The pre-commit hook already runs all three; this hook
# is the backstop that catches `git commit --no-verify` and any drift
# between what was last committed and what's about to be pushed.
#
# `pnpm run doctor` composes typecheck + lint + test:fast --run.
# **The `run` is load-bearing.** `pnpm doctor` (without `run`) hits
# pnpm's built-in `doctor` command — a project-health diagnostic that
# silently no-ops here — instead of the script in package.json. The
# branch shipped with that bug for a stretch and CI caught failures
# the pre-push hook should have caught locally; the explicit `run`
# eliminates the precedence ambiguity.
pnpm run doctor

